'''Camarles''' is a [[municipality]] in the [[Comarques of Catalonia|''comarca'']] of the [[Baix Ebre]] in [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]]. It was created in 1978 from parts of the municipality of [[Tortosa]]. It is situated in the east of the ''comarca'', near the head of the [[Ebro|Ebre]] [[Delta (geography)|delta]]. The town is served by the N-340 road to Tortosa, which also connects it with the AP-7 [[Motorway|''autopista'']] at either [[l'Aldea]] to the south or [[l'Ampolla]] to the north.

